Hey <@U028F34L5KJ>

You can customize the design for the pop-up form but unfortunately, styling for the pop-up form is very limited. However, if you on your team will able to add to the stylesheet of your site or just the pages you'll have the pop-up form on you can add some CSS to style the form yourself.

Something like this:
```.leadinModal.leadinModal-theme-default.leadinModal-v3 .dyno-image {
    float: none;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto 10px;
    width: 100%;
}
.leadinModal .dyno-image img {
    max-width: 100%;
}
.leadinModal.leadinModal-theme-default.leadinModal-v3.leadinModal-preview h4,
.leadinModal.leadinModal-theme-default.leadinModal-v3.leadinModal-preview .advance-wrapper {
    margin-left: 0;
    text-align: center;
}```
Note:
With a bit of CSS styling and overrides, you can get the popup form to look more like a popup. by above with CSS styles should get you in the right direction. It's not ideal to modify a popup for but it does the trick if you didn't want to go with a nonHubSpot solution.

Let me know if there have any other follow-up queries. Thanks!

